⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Doris Vinyard
node AHX · AHX · ⟦Doris Vinyard:AHX:1c14a7⟧

WHO   — Doris Vinyard — the mother who watches it take her sons
WHAT  — The family's grief in real time: a parent forced to see what was planted at her own table grow into something that kills.
WHERE — AHX · American History X (1998)  Framework inputs: American History X (1998, dir. Tony Kaye, New Line); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the cost of the hatred is domestic, and she is the one who pays it in fear.
HOW   — By failing to stop what a dead husband's prejudice began, and loving her sons through the ruin of it.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I buried their father and watched his worst lesson outlive him in my boys. A mother can love and still be powerless.

